sfaction,and improved quality oflifeSong feizhouDefinition-focus,objectives and approach? The approach of HF is the systematicapplication of relevant information abouthuman capabilities,limitations,characteristics,behavior,and motivation to the design ofthings and procedures people use and theenvironments in which they use themSong feizhouDefinition? Human factors discovers and appliesinformation about human behavior,abilities,and other characteristics to thedesign of tools,machines,systems,tasks,jobs,and environments for productive,safe,comfortable,and effective humanuseSong feizhouHistory? Early history? Late 1800s and early 1900s,Frank and Lillian Gilbreth��s work? During WWII,it became clear that,even with the best selectionand training,the operation of some of the complex equipment stillexceeded the capabilities of the people who had to operate it,Itwas time to reconsider fitting the equipment to the person? 1945 to 1960,The Birth of a Profession? 1949,the Ergonomics Research Society (now called ErgonomicsSociety) was formed in Britain,and the first book on humanfactors was published,entitled Applied Experimental Psychology,Human Factors in Engineering Design? 1957 was an important year,especially for HF in the United States? Journal Ergonomics appeared in US? The HF Society was formed? 1959,International Ergonomics Association was formedSong feizhouHistory? 1960 to 1980,A period of RapidGrowth?Race for Space,military industry?Expanded to many companies?Pharmaceuticals?Computers?Automobiles?Other consumer productsSong feizhouHistory? 1980 to 1990,Computers,Disasters,and Litigation? Computer? Ergonomically designed computer equipment? User-friendly software? Human factors in offices? Disasters? 1979.3,Three Mile Island�� �������� �� nuclear power station incident? 1984.12.4,a leak of methylisocyanate(MIC) at the Union Carbidepesticide plant in Bhopal,India,claimed the lives of nearly 4000 andinjured another 200,000? 1986,an explosion and fire at the Chernobyl (�